{"id":500,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Thomas Cruise Mapother IV (born July 3, 1962)Â is an American actor and film producer. Regarded as aÂ HollywoodÂ icon,Â he has receivedÂ various accolades, including anÂ Honorary Palme d'OrÂ and threeÂ Golden Globe Awards, in addition to nominations for fourÂ Academy Awards. As of 2025,Â his filmsÂ have grossed overÂ $13.3 billionÂ worldwide, placing him among theÂ highest-grossing actorsÂ of all time. One of Hollywood's mostÂ bankable stars, he is consistently one of the world'sÂ highest-paid actors.\n\nCruise began acting in the early 1980s and made his breakthrough with leading roles inÂ Risky BusinessÂ (1983) andÂ Top GunÂ (1986), the latter earning him a reputation as aÂ sex symbol.Â Critical acclaim came with his roles in the dramasÂ The Color of Money (1986),Â Rain ManÂ (1988), andÂ Born on the Fourth of JulyÂ (1989). For his portrayal ofÂ Ron KovicÂ in the latter, he won aÂ Golden Globe AwardÂ . He received a nomination for theÂ Academy Award for Best Actor. As a leading Hollywood star in the 1990s, he starred in commercially successful films, including the dramaÂ A Few Good MenÂ (1992), the thrillerÂ The FirmÂ (1993), the horror filmÂ Interview with the VampireÂ (1994), and the sports comedy-dramaÂ Jerry MaguireÂ (1996); for the latter, he won aÂ Golden Globe Award for Best ActorÂ and his second nomination for the Academy Award for Best Actor. Cruise's performance in the dramaÂ MagnoliaÂ (1999) earned him anotherÂ Golden Globe AwardÂ and a nomination for theÂ Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor.\n\nCruise subsequently established himself as a star ofÂ science fictionÂ andÂ action films, often performing his risky stunts. He played fictional agentÂ Ethan HuntÂ in eightÂ Mission: ImpossibleÂ films, beginning withÂ Mission: ImpossibleÂ (1996) and ending withÂ Mission: Impossible â€“ The Final ReckoningÂ (2025).Â His other films in the genre includeÂ Vanilla SkyÂ (2001),Â Minority ReportÂ (2002),Â The Last SamuraiÂ (2003),Â Collateral (2004),Â War of the WorldsÂ (2005),Â Knight and DayÂ (2010),Â Jack ReacherÂ (2012),Â OblivionÂ (2013),Â Edge of TomorrowÂ (2014), andÂ Top Gun: MaverickÂ (2022).\n\nCruise holds theÂ Guinness World RecordÂ for the most consecutiveÂ $100-million-grossing movies, a feat that was achieved from 2012 to 2018. In December 2024, he was awarded theÂ US Navy's highest civilian honor, theÂ Distinguished Public Service Award, in recognition of his \"outstanding contributions\" to the military, with his screen roles.Â ForbesÂ ranked him as the world's most powerful celebrity in 2006.Â He was namedÂ People'sÂ Sexiest Man AliveÂ in 1990,Â and received the top honour of \"Most Beautiful People\" in 1997.Â Outside his film career, Cruise has been an outspoken advocate forÂ the Church of Scientology, which has resulted in controversy and scrutiny of his involvement in the organisation. An aviation enthusiast, he has held aÂ pilot certificateÂ since 1994.","name":"Tom Cruise","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"FranÃ§ais","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"Tom Cruise est un acteur et producteur amÃ©ricain, nÃ© le 3 juillet 1962 Ã  Syracuse dans l'Ã‰tat de New York.\n\nAprÃ¨s avoir interprÃ©tÃ© des seconds rÃ´les, notamment dans Taps et Outsiders, il obtient son premier rÃ´le important dans la comÃ©die dramatique Risky Business en 1983, mais c'est aprÃ¨s avoir interprÃ©tÃ© Pete Â« Maverick Â» Mitchell dans Top Gun (1986) qu'il devient une star internationale. Depuis, il a jouÃ© dans de nombreux films Ã  succÃ¨s, tels que Rain Man, NÃ© un 4 juillet, Entretien avec un vampire et les cinq Ã©pisodes de la saga Mission impossible.","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"RS","iso_639_1":"sr","name":"Srpski","english_name":"Serbian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Ğ¢Ğ¾Ğ¼ ĞšÑ€ÑƒĞ·","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","iso_639_1":"pt","name":"PortuguÃªs"